he precipitation type. The results allow, for the first time, derivation of an adjustment function based on measurements above 7 m s$^{\textrm{‚àí1}}$. This extended validity of the adjustment function shows a stabilization of the wind-induced precipitation loss for higher wind speeds.{\textless}/p{\textgreater}},
